{"id": 7010, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2017", "session": "17N", "subtopic": "17-1-the-equilibrium-law", "title": "17N.1.HL.TZ0.23", "topic_id": "17", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>At 700 ºC, the equilibrium constant, <em>K</em><sub>c</sub>, for the reaction is 1.075 × 10<sup>8</sup>.</p>\n<p>2H<sub>2</sub> (g) + S<sub>2</sub> (g) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> 2H<sub>2</sub>S (g)</p>\n<p>Which relationship is always correct for the equilibrium at this temperature?</p>\n<p>A. [H<sub>2</sub>S]<sup>2</sup> &lt; [H<sub>2</sub>]<sup>2</sup> [S<sub>2</sub>]</p>\n<p>B. [S<sub>2</sub>] = 2[H<sub>2</sub>S]</p>\n<p>C. [H<sub>2</sub>S] &lt; [S<sub>2</sub>]</p>\n<p>D. [H<sub>2</sub>S]<sup>2</sup> &gt; [H<sub>2</sub>]<sup>2</sup>[S<sub>2</sub>]</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}